There you go.

93
00:03:58,380 --> 00:03:59,610
莫菲去哪儿了
Where the hell is Murphy?

94
00:03:59,910 --> 00:04:03,110
骨折很严重  但不需要钢钉
It's a severe fracture, but I don't think you'll need pins.

95
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:05,170
年轻人的骨头愈合能力很好
Young bones tend to heal very well.

96
00:04:05,170 --> 00:04:06,070
「年轻人的骨头」
Young Bones?

97
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:08,610
那不是「星际迷航: 原初」的漫画小说吗
Isn't that a "Star Trek: Origins" graphic novel?

98
00:04:11,370 --> 00:04:12,460
我不知道
I'm not sure.

99
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:15,390
不  我开玩笑的
No, that was a joke.

100
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:16,800
你的父母在哪儿
Where are your parents?

101
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,740
他们在路上了
They're coming.

102
00:04:17,740 --> 00:04:20,240
他们在市里上班  所以开过来有点远
They both work in the city, so it's a long drive for them.

103
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:22,130
我本来在参加野外考察
I was on a school field trip,

104
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:23,860
结果自己绊倒了
and I tripped over my own feet.

105
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:26,580
竟然正好摔在谢尔比·洛马尔面前
Of course, it was right in front of Shelby Lomar.

106
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:27,990
至少样子非常狼狈
At least it was pretty gross,

107
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:30,300
所以我起码得了点同情分
so I got some sympathy points for that.

108
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:36,730
我还以为你的骨折是由更严重的事故造成的
I would expect this to have been caused by a more serious accident.

109
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:37,790
不  就是绊倒了
Nope, just a trip.

110
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:38,950
我经常绊倒
I do that a lot.

111
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:39,980
我也很无奈
What can I say?

112
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:41,000
我笨手笨脚的
I'm clumsy.

113
00:04:41,410 --> 00:04:43,480
好  盯着我的手指
Yes. Now follow my finger.

114
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:53,550
你有点眼球震颤和不自主眼运动
You have some nystagmus -- an involuntary eye movement.

115
00:04:53,550 --> 00:04:55,190
什么意思
So what's that mean?

116
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:57,500
你摔倒时伤到头了吗
When you fell, did you hit your head?

117
00:04:57,590 --> 00:04:58,300
没有
No.

118
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,070
你觉得我有脑损伤吗
What, you think I have brain damage?

119
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:02,940
眼球震颤可能是神经系统问题的症状
Nystagmus can be a sign of a neurological issue.

120
00:05:03,490 --> 00:05:06,340
难怪我在社会调研里只得了C
Well, that would explain the "C" I got in social studies.

121
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,810
你又在开玩笑吧
That was another joke, wasn't it?

122
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:14,430
我去给你预约脑部CT
I'm going to order a head CT for you.

123
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:15,280
去吧
Go for it.

124
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:21,730
-肖恩  你睡觉了吗  -睡了
- Shaun, are you getting any sleep? - Yes.

125
00:05:21,730 --> 00:05:23,760
是吗  真的睡觉了吗
Really? I mean, really getting sleep?

126
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,060
我准时到了医院
I got here on time.

127
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:26,050
那很好
Well, that's good.

128
00:05:26,050 --> 00:05:28,160
我用了任意门
I used a teleportation device.

129
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:34,890
麻烦给我放射科表单
Radiology form, please.

130
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:41,760
肖恩  那个男孩看起来很像...
Shaun, that boy, he looks like...

131
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,790
史蒂夫  没错
Steve. He does.

132
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:45,550
他们有血缘关系吗
Is he related?

133
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,910
他叫埃文·格里克  应该没有
His name is Evan Gallico, so I don't think so.

134
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:52,820
这太不可思议了
That is uncanny.

135
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:54,230
只是巧合而已
Just coincidental.

136
00:05:54,230 --> 00:05:56,510
他跟你弟弟简直一模一样
He looks exactly like your brother.

137
00:05:56,510 --> 00:05:57,340
并不是完全一样
No, he doesn't.

138
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:58,760
他的头发短一些
His hair is shorter.

139
00:05:59,410 --> 00:06:01,600
我被吓到了  你没被吓到吗
It freaks me out. It doesn't freak you out?

140
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,360
没有
No.

141
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,120
吓到了也没关系
It's okay if it does --

142
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,460
不  他不是史蒂夫  史蒂夫已经死了
No, he's not Steve. Steve's dead.

143
00:06:10,150 --> 00:06:12,720
我说「我用了任意门」是玩笑话
"I used a teleportation device" was a joke.

144
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,810
那...很好
Yeah, that's...that's good.

145
00:06:25,910 --> 00:06:30,440
我没能参加妈妈的葬礼是因为我恋爱了
So, I couldn't come to Mom's funeral because I fell in love.

146
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,960
她也是学校里的老师
She was another teacher at the school.

147
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,290
一个泰国女人
A Thai woman.

148
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:37,670
她很善良
And she was kind and --

149
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:40,330
美丽  有爱心...
and beautiful and loving...

150
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:43,660
但病得很重
and very, very sick.

151
00:06:45,070 --> 00:06:47,310
她有先天性心脏缺损
She had a congenital heart defect.

152
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:56,450
如果你不愿意告诉我
Look, if you don't want to tell me

153
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:58,630
这六个月你去哪里了  那就别说
where you've been for the last six months, then don't.

154
00:06:58,630 --> 00:06:59,590
这是你的事
It's your business.

155
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:01,390
但是别侮辱我的智商
But don't insult my intelligence.

156
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:02,710
我不能丢下她
Well, I couldn't just leave her.

157
00:07:02,710 --> 00:07:05,520
你连花五分钟打个电话的时间都没有吗
You couldn't leave her for five minutes to make a phone call?

158
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:08,660
打扰到你们了吗
This a bad time?

159
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:11,750
没有  请进
No, come in.

160
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:19,610
CT结果显示  你的胰腺有病变
According to the CT, you have a lesion on your pancreas.

161
00:07:19,610 --> 00:07:21,180
可能是什么病变
Well, what do you think this lesion could be?

162
00:07:21,180 --> 00:07:22,090
还不确定
Not sure.

163
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,650
所以我们需要做病理切片检查
That's why we need to biopsy it.

164
00:07:23,930 --> 00:07:25,990
可能只是个良性囊肿
It could just be a benign cyst.

165
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:26,810
或者
Or...?

166
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:27,530
或者
Or...

167
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:31,180
可能是癌症  对吗
it could be cancer, right?

168
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:33,730
我们很快就能知道了
We'll know soon enough.

169
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:52,500
这很快的
This won't take long.

170
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,670
我知道  我已经做过两次了
I know. I've had two of these.

171
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:56,590
再来一次我就能有童军勋章了
One more and I get my Scout badge.

172
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:01,760
这很好笑
That was funny.

173
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,420
没看到你的表情  很难说
Tough to tell without looking at you,

174
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:05,660
但我猜你在讽刺我
but I'm guessing that was sarcasm.

175
00:08:05,940 --> 00:08:08,100
不是  我有自闭症
No. I have autism,

176
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:10,840
